verbose_text: The results indicate a stimulatory effect of infection on IGF-I and TNF-alpha gene expression in the spleen : IGF-I was elevated 6.802-fold (p = 0.0001) at Day 3 after infection with 10 6 colony forming unit (CFU) of Yersinia ruckeri [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] and TNF-alpha gene expression 60.497-fold (p = 0.001) as compared with the uninfected control [XREF_BIBR].
